    <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 text-center">Irrigation in the Desert</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Water in Las Cruces is expensive and getting more so. The city enforces mandatory watering schedules that change by season, and violations come with fines. A poorly designed irrigation system wastes water, costs you money, and can damage the landscape it's supposed to support — overwatering in caliche soil creates standing water that rots roots and attracts pests.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">A well-designed system does the opposite. It delivers the right amount of water to the right zones at the right times — spray heads for turf, drip emitters for beds and trees, smart controllers that adjust automatically based on weather and season. Everything stays within the city's watering schedule without you having to think about it.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">David is NDS Pro Certified and has been designing and installing irrigation systems in the Mesilla Valley for over 19 years. He knows which heads work in our water pressure, which drip emitters hold up in the heat, and how to zone a system so nothing gets too much or too little water.</p>
